Interface IFetchResult


  • public interface IFetchResult
    The result of a multi-item or multi-state fetch method from com.ibm.team.repository.service.IRepositoryItemService.
    Since:
    0.7

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List getMissingItems()
      Returns all missing items in a list.
      java.util.List getNotFoundItems()
      Return a list containing all items that the fetch call could not find
      java.util.List getPermissionDeniedItems()
      Return a list containing all of the items requested in the fetch for which the current user was denied permission to read.
      java.util.List getRetrievedItems()
      Return a list containing all items that the fetch call retrieved.
      boolean hasMissingItems()
      Returns true if the fetch could not retrieve any of the requested items for any reason.
      boolean hasNotFoundItems()
      Returns true if any of the requested items to the fetch call were not found.

      Returns true if the user was denied permission to read any of the requested items.

        java.util.List getMissingItems()
        Returns all missing items in a list. This is the union of the permissionDeniedItems and the notFoundItems lists. Provided for backwards compatibility: previous users of FetchResult would expect all items missing for any reason to be in this list.
